<h1>JavaScript Numbers</h1>
<h2>The Number.isSafeInteger() Method</h2>

<p>Number.isSafeInteger() returns true if a value is a safe integer and of datatype Number:</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<p>Number.isSafeInteger() is not supported in Internet Explorer.</p>

<script>
let result =
"Is 123 a safe integer? " + Number.isSafeInteger(123) + "<br>" +
"Is +123 a safe integer? " + Number.isSafeInteger(-123) + "<br>" +
"Is '123' a safe integer? " + Number.isSafeInteger('123');

document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = result;
</script>

</body>
